### Level 0 — The Swamp of POX (RPC over HTTP)
### Everything goes through one endpoint, method is always POST
### No use of HTTP semantics

POST http://api.example.com/service HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{ "action": "getCustomer", "id": "C-001" }

---

POST http://api.example.com/service HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{ "action": "createCustomer", "name": "Acme Ltd", "email": "acme@example.com" }

---

POST http://api.example.com/service HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{ "action": "deleteCustomer", "id": "C-001" }
